    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-10T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-10T06:00:00-05:00" n="592"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d592">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.20/482: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_SLA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-10T14:00:00+03:00"
                            >September 10, 1939—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 10—10:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>525. My 535 [<hi rend="italic">523</hi>], September 9, 10 p.m. The press today
                    publishes under the title “The Partial Calling up of Reserves to the Red Army”,
                    a Tass communiqué of which the following is a full translation: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In connection with the German-Polish war which is assuming an
                            increasingly extensive and threatening character, the Government in the
                            interest of the further strengthening of the defense of the country has
                            decided on partial calling up to the army of certain classes. The
                            summoning of reserves to the Red Army has been carried out in the
                            Ukraine, White Russia, Moscow, <persName corresp="#p_KMI1"
                                >Kalinin</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_OVM1">Orlov [<hi
                                    rend="italic">Orel</hi>]</persName> military districts.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>The above announcement was presumably provoked by the press reports from Moscow
                    concerning the measures taken by the Soviet Government and as will be observed
                    reveals little in regard to the purpose of the partial mobilization or the areas
                    of the western frontier to which reinforcements are being sent. From the syntax
                    of the last paragraph it would appear that the summoning of reserves in the
                    military districts indicated has been completed. As a result of the
                    commandeering of non-military motor vehicles there is noticeably less traffic in
                    Moscow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
